        {
            "title": "Venture Global Shares Sink After BP Wins Arbitration Case Over LNG Dispute",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Connor Hart </p><br/><p>\n  Shares of Venture Global tumbled after the U.S. natural-gas exporter suffered a surprising loss in an arbitration case against customer BP. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The stock fell 19% to $10.25 in premarket trading Friday. Shares had their public debut in January and opened trading at $24.05 apiece, down 3.8% from their $25 IPO price. </p><p>\n\n  BP was issued a partial final award by the International Chamber of Commerce's International Court of Arbitration, Venture Global said in a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission late Thursday. </p><p>\n\n  The award found that Venture Global had breached its obligations to declare a commercial operation date at its Calcasieu Pass liquefied natural gas facility in Louisiana in a timely manner and act as a \"reasonable and prudent operator\" pursuant to the companies' sale-and-purchase agreement, along with other obligations. </p><p>\n\n  Separately, Venture Global said it had reached a settlement with another long-term customer that it didn't name. </p><p>\n\n  Venture Global said it is disappointed by the decision, which it believes contradicts findings from its prior arbitration involving Shell, which it settled back in August. </p><p>\n\n  The Arlington, Va., company for about two years has been embroiled in legal fights with some of the world's biggest oil-and-gas companies, who allege Venture Global enriched itself at their expense by withholding cargoes of LNG after Russia's invasion of Ukraine sent natural-gas prices soaring. The customers say Venture Global instead sold the cargoes on the spot market and raked in hefty profits. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Connor Hart at connor.hart@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  10-10-25 0726ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/venture-global-shares-sink-after-bp-wins-arbitration-case-over-lng-dispute-ce7d5adad08df022",
            "pub_date": "2025-10-10 19:30:37",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
